### Swift Enum Raw Values

Raw values provide default values for each enum case. All raw values must be of the same type, and each case must have a unique raw value.

**Raw Value Types:**

Supported raw value types: `Int`, `Float`, `Double`, `String`, `Character`, and any type that conforms to `RawRepresentable`.

```swift
enum StatusCode: Int {
    case ok = 200
    case created = 201
    case moved = 301
    case badRequest = 400
    case notFound = 404
    case serverError = 500
}

// Implicit raw values (auto-incrementing)
enum Weekday: Int {
    case monday = 1, tuesday, wednesday, thursday, friday, saturday, sunday
}
// tuesday = 2, wednesday = 3, etc.

enum Compass: String {
    case north = "N"
    case south = "S"
    case east = "E"
    case west = "W"
}

// Implicit string raw values (same as case name)
enum Planet: String {
    case mercury, venus, earth, mars, jupiter, saturn, uranus, neptune
}
// Planet.earth.rawValue = "earth"
```

**Working with Raw Values:**

| Operation | Syntax | Description |
|-----------|--------|-------------|
| Get raw value | `enumCase.rawValue` | Access the raw value |
| Create from raw | `EnumType(rawValue:)` | Failable initializer |
| Default String | `case name` = case name as string |
| Default Int | Starts from 0 or specified value |

```swift
enum Direction: String {
    case north, south, east, west
}

// Getting raw value
let dir = Direction.north
print(dir.rawValue)  // "north"

// Creating from raw value
if let direction = Direction(rawValue: "east") {
    print("Direction: \(direction)")
}

// Invalid raw value returns nil
let invalid = Direction(rawValue: "unknown")  // nil

// Int with increments
enum Month: Int {
    case january = 1, february, march, april, may, june
    case july, august, september, october, november, december
}

if let month = Month(rawValue: 3) {
    print("Month: \(month)")  // Month: march
}
```

**When to Use Raw vs Associated Values:**

| Feature | Raw Values | Associated Values |
|---------|------------|-------------------|
| Type | Same for all cases | Can differ per case |
| Pre-populated | Yes | No (set at creation) |
| Uniqueness | Must be unique | No constraint |
| Default mapping | Yes | No |

> **Key Point:** Raw values are set at declaration. Associated values are set at initialization. An enum can have either raw values or associated values, but not both.

```swift
// This is NOT allowed
// enum Mixed { case value(Int); case other = 5 }
```

The `init?(rawValue:)` initializer is automatically provided for enums with raw values.

codeExample:
import Foundation

enum HttpMethod: String {
    case get = "GET"
    case post = "POST"
    case put = "PUT"
    case delete = "DELETE"
    case patch = "PATCH"
}

// Using raw values for API calls
func makeRequest(method: HttpMethod, url: String) {
    print("\(method.rawValue) \(url)")
}

makeRequest(method: .get, url: "/api/users")
makeRequest(method: .post, url: "/api/users/create")

// Parsing from raw values
let responseCode = 404
if let status = StatusCode(rawValue: responseCode) {
    print("Status: \(status)")
}

// Implicit Int raw values
enum Priority: Int {
    case low = 1, medium, high, critical
}

print("Low priority: \(Priority.low.rawValue)")
print("Critical priority: \(Priority.critical.rawValue)")

// String raw values with custom mapping
enum Country: String {
    case usa = "United States"
    case gbr = "United Kingdom"
    case jpn = "Japan"
}

if let country = Country(rawValue: "Japan") {
    print("Country code: \(country)")
}
